The INEC Returning Officer for the governorship election in Taraba state, Professor Adamu Iya has postponed the announcement of the election results till tomorrow, Monday by 12noon. He announced the postponement at the INEC state headquarters in Jalingo at about 8.40pm on Sunday. It was observed that results from five local government areas were brought in. However, Prof. Iya said announcement of the governorship election results was postponed till tomorrow but gave no reason. Bayelsa gov poll:  INEC set to announce new date PDP accuses APC of plot to derail Taraba guber poll 2015 Political Events in Retrospective